[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_dwarf_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The bossy woman is not really helpful, but at least she is quiet now. She couldn't feed an animal even if she was a honeycomb in a bear's den. At least she caresses them most of the time. It helps to keep them calm. Even more than it calms her.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_dwarf_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "These precious darlings were meant to peacefully graze on meadows of Rothelio's heart. How do I ever get them through what happened? It is beyond be how they are handling it so well.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "This journey is getting increasingly more exhausting. The good thing is that Justinia found joy in taking care of animals, to everyone's surprise. At least she does not complain all the time or stare mindlessly into distance. I hope this gives her comfort I was unable to give her myself.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I'd try to pet them too, but I'm afraid they might bite back. We're all pretty stressed, both humans and animals. And, well...goblins, droogs, dwarves...well, all of us.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "All these years, these ghouls and ghosts have been raving in their madness just a few hour's walk from our homes. On one side, it would have been safer to be aware of this, but on the other, who could peacefully plant wheat seeds knowing that these nightmarish horrors could just crawl out of the ground? I say we were blessed not to know. Now we're cursed. How can we live everyday lives again?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I think that once we escape, we should all join military. None of us will ever sleep peacefully again. At least we can help others to what we cannot have.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_3_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I admire Marlina's determination, but I am afraind that learning magic skills takes a lot time. How long until we can just explode our enemies? Twenty years? Thirty? I say grabbing a bow is a lot more realistic.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_3_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I don't trust myself enough to join Adoniah and his party in fighting, but at least I can fire arrows in opposite direction. That way I can't hit anyone from group and in this place it's basically impossible to miss.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_4_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I can't wait to invite our droog friends to a tavern. They say they've never tasted beer. Can you believe? I'll show them the greatest of man's inventions. That's the least I can do to repay them.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_4_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I think I'll start brewing my own beer once we get out. I'm curious to try droog ideas. Their minds are unscathed by human knowledge of beer. Imagine, Guildford suggested that beer sounds like something that might taste well with plumes brewed into it.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_big_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "This little goblin fellow is an amazing storyteller. I never heard of Seck Resurgence or The Great Krug Hunt before. They're brilliant stories but I will never believe that a simple farmer was able to destroy a powerful seck leader or that a party of village hunters nearly wiped out the entire krug population.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_man_big_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I feel sorry I was grumpy about Croigord before. A goblin is a better friend to me now than any human was before. I hope I'll be able to find some curious magic item on our way. I think he'd appreciate that.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_woman_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Brayden is right. Having witnessed insane spirits pouncing on us, how can we plow fields, chop pines, or smith horsehoes again? I made my decision. I am going to study combat magic and help removing these horrors from the face of this land. There will be no more peace for me, but it doesn't matter. I know what my destiny is now and I'll follow it.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_woman_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I can already cast Fireball, but that's not enough. To be actually usefull, I'd need to be able to cast Bomb at least. Fireblast would be even better. But so far, I struggle even with Metal Shards.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_woman_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "We spent so much time worrying about ourselves that we didn't even consider how these poor beasts feel. After spending their whole lives working in the fields, they now face horrors even we never knew existed. And the entire time they are defenseless, carrying our wagons. Can you image the horror of that?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_refugee_woman_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "There, there, don't worry. You get to rest now, sweetie. We'll keep you safe.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_droog_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "When Adoniah persuaded me to join him on a ship voyage to hunt some pirates, I never expected to end up dragged into this ghost-fighting madness. As soon as we reach a civilized settlement with a single boat, I'm leaving.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_droog_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Superiority of droog blacksmiths is showing. A plain blade, with no enchantments, yet it cuts through ghosts as if they were dry wood.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_droog_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "First necromantic creatures, now ghosts. Why can't we fight something that drops decent loot for a change?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_droog_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I'm beginning to think we won't make profit from this job. I understand we're protecting helpless peasants from lethal danger, but I was hoping we'd find something valuable along the way. I don't believe anyone ever left this place alive. Sounds like a place to get rich, right?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_goblin_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "My sword and spells may not be very effective against walking spirits, but I was surely very effective in collecting loot from those ruins we passed. Which reminds me...you surely know.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_goblin_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Need potions, I guess? Selling anything else is so tough these days.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_leader_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "If I hadn't personally smashed a ghost with my hammer, I would never have believed that they can be destroyed with mundane means. It would seem that we shouldn't believe all the old stories, huh? My next step will be setting a dragon on fire, hahaha! Don't forget to speak with Lizzith. She'll tell you what needs to be done next.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_leader_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Whatever has the fate prepared for us, we'll face it with courage.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_man_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I've fought dragons, the undead, and vampires. Now I also have a ghost expertise. Can you imagine how famous I am going be?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_man_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The deeper we're getting into this mess, the more fun it is. I believe my sword arm can almost compete with an angry mule's kick.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_woman_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "It's so great that before I became leader of my own party, I get to learn from Adoniah's mistakes. The first rule is never to lead a group of peasants into domain of necromantic arcane monsters. I am quite certain it was a bad idea at this point.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_woman_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The next supreme wizard of the lithids is mine, mark my words. I need to earn my fame before I try to form my own party.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_woman_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "We're just past Uqelian temple. The wraiths pounced on us, so I sealed the passage until you get here. It won't last long, better get ready. Also, once we repel their assault, I ask you to destroy their leader in the temple. His power is immense. Also, in the ruins we passed before, there is a dungeon with mighty enemies. I can see a room with three of those strange creatures composed of stone orbs. If you destroy those too, we can move safely again.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_party_woman_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Remember, destroy the leader of the wraiths and three orb creatures in a single room in the dungeon beneath the ruins we passed earlier.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_seck_guide_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "So, in the heart of darkness we meet again. Your powers are exhausted, your allies destroyed by your own hand, after they had risen as the undead. Noble quest of protecting defenseless refugees has failed. Do you even remember the blockade of poor villages you wanted to break through? Who am I? We've known each other for some time. But not quite enough yet for me to let out my true identity. You'll find out soon. I just wanted to tell you I'm sorry for your loss. It is not the reason to give up, hero. The land still needs you. There are greater dangers than those you have seen so far. And there are not many likes of you to face them.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_15_seck_guide_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "This cave seems sealed, but there is another way from the camp.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
